# Modal dialogs

CRUD and admin dialogs use DaisyUI `<dialog class="modal">` with a **content-sized** inner box.

## Width

Use `modal-box modal-box-fit` on the inner box. **Do not** set `max-w-lg`, `max-w-2xl`, or `max-w-3xl` on dialogs.

`.modal-box-fit` is defined in [`src/routes/layout.css`](src/routes/layout.css) — width follows form content, capped at viewport.

## Structure

```svelte
<dialog bind:this={dialog} class="modal">
	<div class="modal-box modal-box-fit">
		<h3 class="text-lg font-bold">Title</h3>

		<form class="mt-6" onsubmit={handleSubmit}>
			<table class="form-table">
				<tbody>
					<tr>
						<td class="form-table-label">Label</td>
						<td class="form-table-field">
							<input class="input input-bordered w-full max-w-md" />
						</td>
					</tr>
				</tbody>
			</table>

			{#if error}
				<div class="alert alert-error mt-4">
					<span>{error}</span>
				</div>
			{/if}

			<div class="modal-action">
				<button type="button" class="btn btn-ghost">Cancel</button>
				<button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary">Save</button>
			</div>
		</form>
	</div>
	<form method="dialog" class="modal-backdrop">
		<button aria-label="Close dialog">close</button>
	</form>
</dialog>
```

## Rules

- **Loading / error nested dialogs** (e.g. `svelte:boundary` snippets): also use `modal-box modal-box-fit`
- **Fields**: keep `max-w-md` on inputs in `form-table-field` — they set natural dialog width
- **Form layout**: same `form-table` pattern as [`forms-layout.mdc`](forms-layout.mdc), including responsive stacking below `md`

